==â&euro;&lsaquo;In the books==
In the ''[[A Song of Ice and Fire]]'' novels, the [[Dothraki]] are an unsentimental people who do not name their horses or dogs, and Drogo refers to his stallion as his &quot;Red&quot;. When Mirri decides to sacrifice him, [[Rakharo]], [[Aggo]] and Quaro have to force him into the tent as he is frightened of the stench of death. As in the TV series, Mirri slits his throat for her blood magic.

When Daenerys walks into Drogo's funeral pyre, for a moment she glimpses Drogo on his Red.

sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
Drogo rides the Red to [[Pentos]] to meet with [[Illyrio Mopatis]] and [[Viserys Targaryen]] to accept a pact to marry Viserys' sister [[Daenerys Targaryen|Daenerys]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Drogo rides the Red through the [[Dothraki Sea]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Lord Snow]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;, [[Vaes Dothrak]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; and [[Lhazar]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Pointy End]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;.

After suffering a wound from his defiant [[bloodrider]] [[Mago]] and subsequently being treated by the [[maegi]] [[Mirri Maz Duur]], Drogo falls from the Red having grown weak from the festering wound. In a desperate attempt to save him, Daenerys begs Mirri to perform [[blood magic]]. The few bloodriders who remain loyal to him carry Drogo into a tent, and Mirri tells them that only death can pay for life, requesting that they bring her his horse. The Red is uneasy as he is brought in, and Mirri calms him with a chant before slitting his throat.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Baelor]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
